column1388: source:["## Detect and remove outliers in numerical variables"]}
column1418: This function will loop through a list of features and detect outliers in each one of those features. In each\n
column1419: loop, a data point is deemed an outlier if it is less than the first quartile minus the outlier step or exceeds\n
column1420: third quartile plus the outlier step. The outlier step is defined as 1.5 times the interquartile range. Once the \n
column1421: outliers have been determined for one feature, their indices will be stored in a list before proceeding to the next\n
column1422: feature and the process repeats until the very last feature is completed. Finally, using the list with outlier \n
column1423: indices, we will count the frequencies of the index numbers and return them if their frequency exceeds n times.    \n
column1431: outlier_list_col = df[(df[col] < Q1 - outlier_step) | (df[col] > Q3 + outlier_step)].index\n
column1434: multiple_outliers = list(key for key, value in outlier_indices.items() if value > n) \n
